The gun shoots fine, especially with my new magazine. Its accurate with the scope and has no iron sights.

title: For Trade:  Ithaca 37 Featherlight 12ga
postcontent:
Up for trade is a 1970 Ithaca 37 Featherlight Pump Shotgun.  I got it on a whim from a buddy - my grandpa hunted with an Ithaca 37 decades ago and when this one fell into my lap I thought I'd take it in and see what I could do with it.  I half-thought about turning it into a utility gun for around the farm, but after shooting it I can't bring myself to do it - I'd like to see it in the hands of someone who will use it as intended.

This is a smooth shooting field gun - while I'm not a hunter, I took it out to bust some clays and it performed very well.  I already have a nice clay gun though, so as well as this shoots, I just don't have a need for it.  It is one of the models that will pump-fire (ie., hold the trigger, pump, when it falls into battery it will shoot, some say slam-fire) if that's neat to you.

It IS a 1970 field gun, though - the bluing has matured to a worn patina, the wood is worn and has dings and scratches - long story short, while it's a used shotgun, its one heck of a used shotgun that may not be pretty, but is certainly a fantastic shooter.

title: For Sale/Trade:  M&P 9mm FS Insight MRDS, KKM Barrel, 10-8, Apex....more.  temp price drop
postcontent:
Temp price drop to $810 shipped paypal gift.   I am exactly $800 short for a night vision monocular that I found.


I would like to sell, but would prefer to trade for night vision monocular Gen2 or Gen 3 (I will add cash if needed).  Everything is pretty new and in great condition.  I think I listed everything below.  I have over $2,300 invested.  I completely understand that there is no way in hell somebody will pay this amount.

Asking $1300 (paypal as gift or please add 3.5%) OBO don't be afraid to offer, worst I can say is no.

Purchased M&P from a fellow member on this forum and was told gun had under 400rds. I immediately sold the complete slide and purchased a brand new one....Purchased Insight MRDS & Glock Suppressor Sights and sent to Doug Presson Custom Works ( DPCW) for machine work. DPCW milled to accept an Insight MRDS, rear dovetail, 2 ports on each side and 1 port on top and side serrations, "soften" the front for easier holstering and then sand blasted. The sand blast could have been done better b/c there are couple spots that you can kinda see the OEM black coating. I never got a chance to cerakote it, however I kinda like it bare. Once I got my slide back, I installed Apex FSS Kit & FRE, stippled it, undercut the trigger guard and cut 2 circular slots on each side of the grip so that I can remove the stuck mag if jammed (you can kinda see it in the pics, but the magwell covers it up pretty good. Shot it for about 1000 rounds, sold the barrel and purchased a KKM Pro 5" Match Grade Barrel, sent it to HR Barrelworks to cut off 1/2" so that the barrel will extend 1/4". Shot about 500rds, VERY ACCURATE. Then I purchased 10-8 Magwell + 3 TTI Red baseplates + 1 promag 17rd mag. I have not installed TTI baseplate yet b/c I loss the follower, I'll try to find, but if I can't find it you can purchase a new one for about couple bucks. The 10-8 magwell didn't allow mags to drop freely so I sanded and dremeled it until mags dropped free. Also the magwell is screwed on, but I recommend you jb weld it as it can be slight wobble. I can provide detail pics if needed. TTI Baseplates supposed to give you extra 6 rds, but you will need to either use it more or sand the follower a bit so that it can freely move into the baseplate as I could only get extra 4 or 5 rds (can't remember).

title: For Sale:  How to Spot Benchmade Infidel OTF 3300 Black CLONE
postcontent:
I discovered that a Benchmade Infidel that I traded for was actually a fake (didn't find out until I went to sell it and someone pointed it out).  Fortunately, I didn't trade much for it.  Looking around, there seem to be a lot of fakes out there, and plenty of slimeballs selling them as real ones.  I was told by several folks that mine is the best looking fake cone they have seen, so be careful.  Even being a fake, it's still pretty cool.

I've had really good luck with folks on armslist, so hopefully I can provide some tips for spotting them.  Easiest is to go to youtube and search "Benchmade Infidel - Fake Vs. Real."  In summary:

1.  The clip was the only visual giveaway on mind.  The real ones have a butterfly on the bent clip at the tip, and mine does not.  The anodizing of the letters is also different.

2.  The fake ones are a lot heavier.  Of course, you can only tell this if you are buying face to face.  The real ones way about 5 ounces (per manufacturer).  My clone is 7.5 ounces...pretty significant.

3.  There are apparently some other finish differences, though I am told mine is a pretty darn good match.

Hope all this helps.  I am still willing to sell it, if nothing else, to keep this listing active and educate folks.  Do your homework!
